Kisumu Governor Anyang Nyong'o has condoled with the Kisumu boys high-school fraternity following the demise of the Principal Peter Obwogo. Nyong'o noted that the late Obwogo has been an outstanding teacher who has steered the Boys School to greater heights in the national academic map. He said he remembers him as a professional and a resourceful educationist. The Governor further added that since his posting to school, he had worked hard to sustain the school’s national ratings and they will greatly miss him. "On behalf of the people of Kisumu, I wish to send heartfelt condolences to Obwogo’s Family, friends, Kisumu Boy’s high school community, and the Kenya Secondary Schools Headteachers’ Association for this big loss," he said in a statement. The head teachers death at Agah Khan Hospital in Kisumu was confirmed today. Chairman of Kisumu boys school of management Charles Nyakiti who confirmed the death noted that the demise of the principal has left a big gap in the education sector. Nyakiti said they have lost a great teacher, leader and a manager. "Together with the family members we are heading to Busia to deliver our condolences message" he said By the time of his death, Obwogo had declared interest to run for Matayos Parliamentary seat on ODM ticket. He had served the education sector for over 35 years.